{"lemma":"عُصْفُورَةٍ","slug":"عُصْفُورَةٍ","root":"ع.ص.ف.ر","root_slug":"ع-ص-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ص-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29352"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%B5%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"any small bird"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sparrow"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṣapir- (“small bird”), from Proto-Afroasiatic *c̣ipar- (“small bird; guinea fowl”); variant form of صَافِر (ṣāfir, “small bird”), the عُـ (ʕu-) perhaps derives from a conflation with another closely related root Proto-Semitic *ʕVṣṣūr- (“bird”). Compare Hebrew ציפור (ṣippōr), Aramaic צִפְּרָא (ṣippərā), Ugaritic 𐎕𐎔𐎗 (ṣpr), and Akkadian 𒄷 (iṣṣūrum)."},"ipa":["/ʕusˤ.fuːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29352","headword_ar":"عُصْفُورٌ","root":"ESfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSofuwrN","text_ar":"عَصْفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ibn-Rasheek, MF,) but the latter is not an approved form, because there is no chaste word of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEoluwlN","text_ar":"فَعْلُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF, TA,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sparrow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) accord. to AHát, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"same that is called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naq~aAr","text_ar":"نَقَّار"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the male black in the head and neck, the rest of it inclining to ash-colour, with a redness in the wings; the female inclining to yellowness and whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) the word is masc.: (TA:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAfiyru","text_ar":"عَصَافِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) Accord. to Hamzeh, it is so called because it was disobedient, and fled,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaY wafar~a","text_ar":"عَصَى وَفَرَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (MF, TA.) [This, I believe, is said to have been the case when the beasts and birds &c. were summoned before Adam, to be named by him. See the Kur ii. 29-31.] ―         -b2-  [It is also applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any passerine bird."},{"kind":"text","text":"And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSofuwru Aljan~api","text_ar":"عُصْفُورُ الجَنَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The passerine bird of Paradise;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the swallow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxuT~aAfu","text_ar":"الخُطَّافُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISd in TA art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xTf","text_ar":"خطف"},{"kind":"text","text":", and IB in TA art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wT","text_ar":"وط"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  [Also, sometimes,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any small bird."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaArato","text_ar":"طَارَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAfiyru raA^osihi","text_ar":"عَصَافِيرُ رَاْسِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sparrows of his head flew;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov., meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became frightened;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though there were sparrows upon his head when he was still, and they flew away when he was frightened: (Meyd:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inconstant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became angry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAra TaAy^iruhu","text_ar":"طَارَ طَايِرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAy^irN","text_ar":"طَايِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became aged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naq~ato","text_ar":"نَقَّتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAfiyru baTonihi","text_ar":"عَصَافِيرُ بَطْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sparrows of his belly cried"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naq~ato DafaAdiEu biTonihi","text_ar":"نَقَّتْ ضَفَادِعُ بِطْنِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", alluding to the intestines, is also a prov., (TA,) meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, hungry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) In like manner also one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taA^okulo Hat~aY taTiyra EaSaAfiyru baTonika","text_ar":"لَا تَاْكُلْ حَتَّى تَطِيرَ عَصَافِيرُ بَطْنِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Eat thou not until thou be hungry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAfiyru Almuno*iri","text_ar":"اَصَافِيرُ المُنْذِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain excellent camels, that belonged to kings:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain excellent camels that belonged to En-Noamán Ibn-El-Mundhir"},{"kind":"text","text":"were called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAfiyru","text_ar":"اَصَافِيرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uEomaAni","text_ar":"النُّعْمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuSofuwru","text_ar":"العُصْفُورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2065},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male locust."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The king."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the brain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beneath the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farox","text_ar":"فَرْخ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the brain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though separated therefrom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two is a pellicle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain vein in the heart."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IF, O.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A prominent bone in the temple of the horse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the right"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the left;"},{"kind":"text","text":"both being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSofuwraAni","text_ar":"عُصْفُورَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place whence grows the forelock"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A narrow blaze extending downwards from the blaze on the forehead of the horse, not reaching to the muzzle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) ―         -b6-  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAfiyr","text_ar":"عَصَافِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel's hump see expl. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuroSuwfN","text_ar":"عُرْصُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSofuwrN","text_ar":"عُصْفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of wood in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of camel-vehicle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawodaj","text_ar":"هَوْدَج"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniting the extremities of certain"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of wood therein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[perhaps what unites the outer extremities of two long pieces of wood which project horizontally from the lower part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hwdj","text_ar":"هودج"},{"kind":"text","text":", from the two extremities of either side;] (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the form of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAf","text_ar":"اـِكَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of wood which are in the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of camel's saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raHol","text_ar":"رَحْل"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by which the heads of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved pieces of wood called the"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHonaA='","text_ar":"اَحْنَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are fastened"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wood by which are fastened the heads of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of saddle called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qatab","text_ar":"قَتَب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAfiyru","text_ar":"عَصَافِيرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESAfyr","text_ar":"عصافير"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qtb","text_ar":"قتب"},{"kind":"text","text":"are its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaraASiyf","text_ar":"عَرَاصِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":", from which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESAfyr","text_ar":"عصافير"},{"kind":"text","text":"is formed by transposition; and they are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four pins of wood which are put between"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which unite"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conjoin"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heads of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHnA='","text_ar":"احنا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qtb","text_ar":"قتب"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in each"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hinow","text_ar":"حِنْو"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are two of these pins, fastened with sinews or with camel's skin; and in it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appertaining to the same part"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZalifaAt","text_ar":"ظَلِفَات"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nails which unite the head of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qtb","text_ar":"قتب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IDrd:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSofuwr","text_ar":"عُصْفُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the [kind of saddle called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ikaAf","text_ar":"اـِكَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"is its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuroSuwf","text_ar":"عُرْصُوف"},{"kind":"text","text":", from which latter word the former is formed by transposition; and it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of wood fastened between"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uniting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conjoining"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the anterior"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinowaAni","text_ar":"حِنْوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) In a trad. it is said that it it is unlawful to cut or shake off aught from the trees of El-Medeeneh, except for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ESfwr","text_ar":"عصفور"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qtb","text_ar":"قتب"},{"kind":"text","text":", or to supply a sheave of a pulley, or for the handle of an iron implement. (S.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A nail of a ship."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["MF","TA","S","O","K","Msb","Meyd","L","IDrd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}